11:
I'm so nervous. Am I moving my
arms and legs properly?
15:
You are. Don't worry. You have two of
each, and they're working as
intended.
19: Those two are as pretty as a picture.
23:
Almost makes you forget how
they're actually huge goofballs, huh?
34:
What's with all of you? Wait...
Robertson?! From that Liesel fan
club, right? The... Guardian Angels?
37:
That's our OLD name! We're the
Angel-Goddess Alliance, now!
39:
I'm with the "Guardians of the
Goddess" faction. And these guys
are with the "Notice Me, Stella!"
faction.
45:
Shut it, you louse! We've been
around forever!
47:
We don't need you to notice us... Our
only wish is to see Stella live a life full
of joy and—
49:
ANYWAY, what's with that slick dude
who was with her? Ain't it supposed
to be you or Nimbus? What's going
on?! Oh, and one more thing... that
dress was super cute!
52:
Haha! Looks like Nova's good looks
have rubbed some fans the wrong
way. Sorry, fellas. She's taken.
56:
Don't provoke them!
Anyway, you don't need to worry.
Stella hasn't changed at all.
60:
Hehe. That's true... for NOW, at least.
Who knows what the future has in
store, given how many new fans
she's got now!
64: I wonder how things are going...
70: Is that what you really want?
73:
Please don't misunderstand—we
agree wholeheartedly that fighting
should be avoided at all costs. It's
just... It never hurts to be prepared.
75:
There are those who are...
concerned about the Farlands. We
wish to be ready in case something
happens.
77:
And this will help everyone share the
same dream?
80:
D-dream? Uh... Well, in a way, yes. It
will!
83:
In my experience, that can be very
difficult.
86:
There is a proper time and place for
everything. I love this city very much,
so we need to be prepared.
90:
I understand your thoughts about
the Farlands. We can go ahead with
that plan. I hope I can count on your
support.
93:
Sorry to intrude on your lovely
conversation, but I'm not feeling
very well...
95:
O-oh, dear! Come, Luna... Apologies.
We'll have to continue this chat later!
98:
Tch. A simpering little worm hoping
to gain favor with supporters of
anti-Farlands policies. Hardly worth
the breath it takes to speak to him.
106:
How about you, pretty boy? Do you
intend on standing around doing
nothing? The Champion's been
doing patrols of the place—making
you look lazy by comparison.
110:
Well, unlike him, I wasn't appointed
as a knight. Besides, I think all of
these security precautions are a bit
much.
113:
That blonde girl, for example... She
was a ninja, wasn't she? And I have
a feeling there are others—above us,
and on the outside.
120:
So, Nihilyana, can I hear more of
that story from before?
132:
Please. It's as typical a story as you
can imagine. A man and woman
got together, then drifted apart.
That's all there was to it.
135:
And that's the very last you'll hear
about it from me, Stella. That's how
that story ends.
138:
Besides. If you want to talk about
love, why not focus on the two of
you? The heat you're giving off
would make a dragon blush! Do I
detect a budding romance?
145:
I've heard love means putting one
person before everyone else.
152:
Haha. You'd rather keep everyone in
your life equal, then? No special
treatment for anyone?
155:
Love is completely up to you, dear
girl. The level of affection—or
hatred—that you give anyone is
your choice.
165:
I once told someone their existence
was a transgression and they
should vanish. I regret that now.
170:
You can eventually forgive those
you hate. As you said, there is a time
and place for everything.
177:
Perhaps for an unblemished
creature such as yourself, you
should focus on what you "like" the
most. Love can come later.
181:
...Like how Alk said he wanted to
make an omelet shop!
184:
Once all of this is over... What are the
two of us going to do?
189:
I see... I'll think about it. This will be
my homework.
194:
Homework? Why, I'm flattered that
you're embracing your role as my
pupil!
198:
If you're my teacher, may I ask you a
question?
201:
Can something that is broken ever
go back to being how it once was?
205:
No one can turn back time... Though
we can pick up the broken pieces.
What we do with them, however, is
up to us.
216:
Welcome back! It looked incredible.
We could see everything from the
public viewing section.
220:
Yes! Things went very well, but... Who
are those people behind you?
224:
It seems like they're all admirers of
yours, Stella!
228:
Seriously? Are all you brain-dead
humans really that desperate?
Stella deserves way better fans then
the likes of you!
234: Thank you all so much. I'm Stella.
